"[{\"id\":1,\"title\":\"Step Into the Future: ECDS Online Open Forum\",\"description\":\"The ECDS Online Open Forum on August 31, 2024, will introduce the new Confederation, share innovative plans, and offer interactive dialogue with dance sport leaders.\",\"publicationDate\":\"2024-08-22\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"bold\":true,\"text\":\"ECDS Online Open Forum: A New Era for European Dance Sport\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"On August 31, 2024, the European Confederation of Dance Sport (ECDS) will host its first-ever Online Open Forum, an event that promises to redefine the landscape of dance sport in Europe. This landmark gathering is designed to connect, inform, and inspire the entire European dance community, marking a significant milestone for the newly established organization.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"bold\":true,\"text\":\"A Platform for Growth and Innovation\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"The primary goal of the ECDS Online Open Forum is to introduce the dance community to the ECDS, a fresh and dynamic force in European dance sport. During the forum, the Confederation will share its vision, attract new members, and highlight upcoming events and tournaments. This is more than just an introduction—it's an invitation to be part of something new and exciting.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"bold\":true,\"text\":\"A Mobile-First Approach\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"One of the most innovative features of the ECDS is its mobile-first approach. ECDS is set to become the first dance organization fully operable from a smartphone. This modern and convenient design allows members to handle everything—from registering for events to managing their careers—right from their phones. It’s a bold move that reflects the ECDS’s commitment to accessibility and modernity, ensuring that the organization is always within reach.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"bold\":true,\"text\":\"A Unified System for Career Growth\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"ECDS is also launching a groundbreaking global system of career growth. This unified system will bring together all roles within the dance sport industry into a single, cohesive structure. By doing so, it ensures that only qualified individuals can progress to positions such as coaching or refereeing, thus maintaining the highest standards of professionalism and quality in the sport.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"bold\":true,\"text\":\"Engaging Speakers and Interactive Dialogue\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"The forum will feature presentations from the key initiators of the Confederation, members of the Presidium, and leading experts across various fields within dance sport. Designed as a dialogue, this event encourages active participation from attendees. You’ll have the opportunity to ask questions and receive answers directly from the speakers. To ensure your question is addressed, you can submit it during the online registration process. \",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"bold\":true,\"text\":\"Don’t Miss Out!\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Pre-registration is mandatory for all participants and can be completed via this link\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"code\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"https://forms.gle/fgH8X5fycm37B7Dn7\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"The ECDS Online Open Forum is your chance to engage directly with the leaders shaping the future of dance sport in Europe. Mark your calendars for August 31, 2024, and join us as we embark on this exciting new chapter.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"\",\"type\":\"text\"}]}],\"views\":\"61\",\"author\":\"John Deer\",\"pages\":[{\"id\":2,\"name\":\"main\"},{\"id\":3,\"name\":\"ballroom\"},{\"id\":5,\"name\":\"caribbean\"},{\"id\":4,\"name\":\"street\"}],\"tags\":[{\"id\":1,\"tag\":\"Exclusive\"},{\"id\":2,\"tag\":\"Reviews\"},{\"id\":3,\"tag\":\"Fashion\"}]},{\"id\":2,\"title\":\"Test article\",\"description\":\"ECDS elects key officials and plans the First Closed Championship in Athens this December, marking a major step in its strategic direction.\",\"publicationDate\":\"2024-08-19\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Historic Meeting Lays Groundwork for ECDS Future\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Planning and Elections at the Forefront\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"In a pivotal gathering that could shape the future of European competitive dance, representatives from six countries convened to discuss key strategic actions and leadership roles. The meeting, attended by delegates from Estonia, Ukraine, Greece, Bulgaria, Israel, and Georgia, marked a significant step forward for the European Confederation of Dance Sports (ECDS).\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"A Unified Vision: The First Closed Championship in Athens\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"A highlight of the meeting was the unanimous support for Greece's proposal to host the First Closed Championship of the ECDS in Athens this December. This event promises to be a landmark occasion, bringing together top dance athletes from across Europe in a showcase of talent and sportsmanship. The choice of Athens, a city rich in cultural heritage, adds an extra layer of prestige to this championship, and the excitement among the representatives was palpable.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Election of Key Officials\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"The elections held during the meeting were crucial in setting the stage for the ECDS's future direction. Ihor Mashyn of Ukraine was elected as the Vice President of Sports Affais, a role that will see him oversee the development and regulation of competitive dance sports across the continent. Estonia's Ivo Kappet was chosen as the Vice President of the Legal Affairs, a position that will involve ensuring the organization's activities align with international standards and legal frameworks.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Further solidifying the leadership, Georgi Petkov Naydenov from Bulgaria and Theodoros Tsaganos from Greece were elected as members of the Presidium. Their roles will be essential in guiding the ECDS through its upcoming challenges and opportunities.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Future Leadership Decisions Deferred\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"While these appointments were significant, not all positions were filled during the meeting. The election of other officials was postponed to future meetings, indicating a careful and deliberate approach to leadership selection within the ECDS.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Looking Ahead\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"As the ECDS gears up for the First Closed Championship in Athens, the foundation laid at this meeting will be instrumental in its success. With strong leadership in place and a clear vision for the future, the ECDS is poised to make significant strides in the world of competitive dance. The upcoming championship in Athens is expected to be just the beginning of a new era for the organization.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]}],\"views\":\"44\",\"author\":null,\"pages\":[{\"id\":2,\"name\":\"main\"}],\"tags\":[{\"id\":5,\"tag\":\"Popular\"}]},{\"id\":3,\"title\":\"Ballroom Caribbean\",\"description\":\"ECDS elects key officials and plans the First Closed Championship in Athens this December, marking a major step in its strategic direction.\",\"publicationDate\":\"2024-08-19\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Historic Meeting Lays Groundwork for ECDS Future\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Planning and Elections at the Forefront\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"In a pivotal gathering that could shape the future of European competitive dance, representatives from six countries convened to discuss key strategic actions and leadership roles. The meeting, attended by delegates from Estonia, Ukraine, Greece, Bulgaria, Israel, and Georgia, marked a significant step forward for the European Confederation of Dance Sports (ECDS).\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"A Unified Vision: The First Closed Championship in Athens\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"A highlight of the meeting was the unanimous support for Greece's proposal to host the First Closed Championship of the ECDS in Athens this December. This event promises to be a landmark occasion, bringing together top dance athletes from across Europe in a showcase of talent and sportsmanship. The choice of Athens, a city rich in cultural heritage, adds an extra layer of prestige to this championship, and the excitement among the representatives was palpable.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Election of Key Officials\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"The elections held during the meeting were crucial in setting the stage for the ECDS's future direction. Ihor Mashyn of Ukraine was elected as the Vice President of Sports Affais, a role that will see him oversee the development and regulation of competitive dance sports across the continent. Estonia's Ivo Kappet was chosen as the Vice President of the Legal Affairs, a position that will involve ensuring the organization's activities align with international standards and legal frameworks.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Further solidifying the leadership, Georgi Petkov Naydenov from Bulgaria and Theodoros Tsaganos from Greece were elected as members of the Presidium. Their roles will be essential in guiding the ECDS through its upcoming challenges and opportunities.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Future Leadership Decisions Deferred\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"While these appointments were significant, not all positions were filled during the meeting. The election of other officials was postponed to future meetings, indicating a careful and deliberate approach to leadership selection within the ECDS.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"Looking Ahead\",\"type\":\"text\"}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"children\":[{\"text\":\"As the ECDS gears up for the First Closed Championship in Athens, the foundation laid at this meeting will be instrumental in its success. With strong leadership in place and a clear vision for the future, the ECDS is poised to make significant strides in the world of competitive dance. The upcoming championship in Athens is expected to be just the beginning of a new era for the organization.\",\"type\":\"text\"}]}],\"views\":\"45\",\"author\":\"Robert Williams\",\"pages\":[{\"id\":3,\"name\":\"ballroom\"},{\"id\":5,\"name\":\"caribbean\"}],\"tags\":[{\"id\":4,\"tag\":\"History\"}]}]"
